attributes.descriptionHtml:
Tessie was born 8/23/2005 and is a little teaser. She is very friendly but seems to be afraid of dogs and a little intimidated by aggressive cats. Tessie just wants to be a lap cat and have someone play with her. She had been locked in a cage for almost a year but is now running free in a foster home.

Although she is getting up in age and is now in the first stages of CKD, she can still be active and loves to play.  However, you do not have to worry about her climbing your curtains or furniture because she is "Mature", and mature cats don't do those things.

Tess has been in foster care since she was a baby.  She really needs a lifetime family of her own.

If you want more information, please send an email to paws@oplink.net.  Our website is www.pawsrescue.org where each rescued pet has its own webpage.

CLEMENTINE is a lover!  This kitty purrs the moment you touch her...and doesn't stop.  She's just happy all the time.  She loves to wander around the house and rub on your legs.  She also loves to be held and cuddled.  Clementine suffers from CH or Wobbly Cat Syndrome.  The good news is that most  cats  with mild to moderate  cerebellar hypoplasia  can lead relatively normal lives with a little extra  help  from their owners.  She will need a kind and caring family to love her (DOB 02/2021).


**See videos on her page**

Apply to adopt:  https://spaythestrays.rescuegroups.org/forms/form?formid=5596

More about CH:  CH/Wobbly Cat Syndrome (rescuegroups.org)

attributes.descriptionHtml: Tinker is a sweet senior boy who loves to talk to you and enjoys being on a screen porch or in front of a window to enjoy the outside sites. He loves to be brushed, but he does have a habit of licking his hair on his underbelly.  In 2020 Tinker had a growth removed that was diagnosed as squamous cell carcinoma but all was removed and he is doing fine. He has been declared cancer-free. He also was diagnosed with stomatitis and gets a couple of injections as needed every couple of months or can be longer intervals as needed. Tinker needs a family who is able to give him the care he needs and to help him live out his senior years in love and comfort. Tinker and Bell are siblings and must be adopted together.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
My name is Bella, and I'm a 4-1/2year-old female American Staffordshire terrier and American bulldog mix. My mom was found at a boat launch in the middle of winter, just days before giving birth. A kind lady took her in and began socializing me and my siblings as soon as we arrived. My mom and most of my siblings have been adopted, but my sister Bianca and I are still looking for our "forever" homes. Although it's nice here at my foster home, I would love to have a home of my very own.

I'm a little shy with new situations and people, but I warm up quickly. I love to splash in my pool and play fetch. I'm okay with dogs my size, but I would do best in a home without small dogs or cats. My ideal adopter would be experienced with dogs, preferably of my size or breed. My foster mom says I'm crate-trained and I walk well on a leash.

For more information, please email Laura.Adams70345@gmail.com.

HOPE for Animals' dog adoption fee is $100. This includes initial vaccinations and spay/neuter. All dogs adopted through HOPE must have a fenced yard. Other pets in the household must be spayed/neutered and a good vet reference is required.

Up To Date on Vaccines – Yes

FELV Test - Negative

Friendly - Yes / Out Going - Yes

Good for inexperienced Owner - Yes

Litter Trained - Yes

More about me:

Peter has beautiful markings, he is a very handsome cat and he knows it. He carries himself very proudly. He is playful but also a no nonsense kind of boy. He gets along with most of the cats, but a few he does not care for. Peter like all of the outside cats has access to a heated indoor cat area, in cold weather he likes to go in at times, but seems to enjoy finding a warm place in the hay barn. I bet if Peter had his very own forever home he would enjoy being inside lounging around as a couch potato. Peter is a great hunter and would love to live on a farm where he can enjoy being inside and outside. Peter would do best in a home with no small children he does not care much for being carried around. Please consider adopting this handsome cat into your home and heart.

If you’re interested in Peter go to www.olivebranchwv.org and fill out an online application. Someone will get back to you ASAP. You can also come and visit him, or call 304-652-1010 for more information

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Update Octpber 2012:  Bertha is a great dog with a wonderful personality.  She is learning her basic commands and is doing really well.

Bertha, named after the patron saint of female illnesses, was rescued because she was bred to a much too large of a male dog AND then they were puilled forceibly separared by dumb humans.  Her insides were hanging out for over two (2) weeks BEFORE the "owner who loved her"! came to us and said his dog was in trouble. Bertha has successfully gone through surgery and is recooperating well.  She told us she does NOT want to go back to her old family!  She has now been spayed and our vet has declared her "good to go". BERTHA WANTS ALL TO KNOW SHE HAS LEARNED TO "SIT" FOR HER FOOD!!

PHS:1498  http://www.pontchartrainhumanesociety.org/adoption.html

Age:est DOB May 2008
Size (when grown):Medium 40 lbs
Our $100 dog adoption fee covers sterilization and routine vaccinations. ALL our foster dogs are receiving heartworm medication prevention on the 1st of each month.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
I came up to eat with my sister when I was about 4 weeks old, and all of the sudden I ws scruffed by the trapper, who ended up being my foster mom.  She socialized me so I could be adoptable!  

I love to put my paw on your face (of course, with my claws tucked in!)  to get your attention...and what that really means is PET ME!!!!   If you ignore me, then I begin to tap, tap, tap on your face two to three times.  If that doesn't work, I just have to continue my tapping and staring at you until you respond!!!  Sometimes I just like being on your chest with my head on your shoulder.  Bottom line - just love on me, For Pete's Sake!!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Sprite is spayed, tested negative for FIV/FeLV, and is up-to-date on shots. Born Feb. 2010.

Sprite is one of NAR's long term fosters. This little lady is a low key kitty! We think Sprite has been around for a while because she doesn't go to events. She's quite the homebody who gets pretty stressed with the temporary change of environment. Sprite would be happiest in an adult only household where she could be queen of the castle! She gets along with other cats, but would also be just fine being the only cat in the home. She'll come running to greet you at the door and sleep next to you at night. If you're looking for some quiet companionship, beautiful Sprite fits the bill!

***

Sprite was trapped in Northeast Philadelphia during a TNR.  When she first came into foster care we weren't sure how Sprite would adjust. Since she was probably born outside, she was very shy of people and not very trusting. To our delight, Sprite decided that humans are okay and even bring her a little joy which of course includes cat treats!  We think playing with the feather toy is her favorite game. When she finally needs some rest, she jumps in bed with her foster mom and purrs away.

If you're interested in adopting Sprite, please fill out an application at nar.rescuegroups.org

My name is Bandita.  I was adopted out to a family when I was just a wee one with my brother, Leornardo de Catio.  When they moved to a new house, they returned us to our foster mom.  We were really scared and it took us awhile to adjust to the new, old home. 

We both grew to be large cats with the softest fur ever!  Both of us are gentle, but I'm still a little skiddish of small children because of my experience with the other family.  I would like an adult family or just a nice lady to love me forever and keep me safe.  In return, I promise to be the best cat ever.  Won't you consider me for your forever home?

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Love bug alert!

Troy calls to you when he needs attention, which is pretty often. He was originally fostered in a family full of active kids, and for six weeks, his feet never touched the ground. Yes, a true totable cat, Troy also loves to play and is one of the first to cuddle up at bedtime.

Although still a little shy with strangers, once he knows you, Troy just flops over and purrs, purrs, purrs. He's truly a love bug with a huge heart.

One of his favorite toys is the feathered toy on a string. He loves to dance with the toy, wrestle it into submission, or chase after it until he leaps on it with all his strength.

Handsome Troy's stripes are very tight and cute on his head, but on his sides are more like dots. He's a brilliant orange, handsome, cute, with a nice long tail that says, "Here I am!"

What Troy really wants now is a loving, forever family of his own.  He'd prefer a home with another playful cat friend. 

Would you love to learn more about this wonderful "Troy Boy" - maybe come to meet him? For more information, email his foster dad directly at haroldw1@sbcglobal.net. To meet this boy, go to his webpage on our website at www.happycatadoptions.org to fill out an online application.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Our website is updated daily

Zoe is spayed, UTD on vaccines and tested negative for FIV/FeLV. Approx. DOB is June 26, 2010.

*Experienced owner with veterinary references required.*

Some day, I'm going to write my autobiography. It might take a while, since I'm a cat and all, but I have lots of stories to share with the world.
 
It all started when I was just a baby. My brother and I ventured out on our own at just three-weeks of age. Well, now I know why kittens are supposed to stay with their mama until they are at least eight-weeks-old. We ended up trapped in a window well, which was rapidly filling with water during a tropical storm.
 
Luckily, we were rescued, and I'm am still here to tell my tail...err, tale. Since then, I've been living in a foster home. I've met lots of other cats, and boy do I have some funny stories!
 
Speaking of funny- my foster mom says I have a great sense of humor. I like to play with the laces on her shoes- while she's still wearing them-and lick her finger when she pets me.
 
I love getting pets, and curling up with my foster family in bed. When it comes to new people though, I'm quite bashful! It takes me a while to warm up to new people and new situations, and I will need a nice looong acclimation period when I go to my forever home. I get along great with other cats, so I'd love to have a brother or sister.
 
So, here's the first chapter in my story- I hope you will be a part of my next chapter!

If you're interested in adopting Zoe, please fill out an application at www.nar.rescuegroups.org.
attributes.name: Zoe *Video

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Narissa was one of three kittens that were left at our vets office.  They were 2-3 weeks old at the time, so she was a bottle baby.  She's a very sweet and attentive girl.  Narissa will sit next to you and just nuzzle at you, or kneed you with her front paws.  She enjoys stretching out and watching what is going on, although sometimes she is in the middle of what is going on!
 
Narissa is sometimes a little hard-headed in that you can keep nudging her off the arm of the couch and she'll just keep coming right back up!
 
She had a bad case of Feline Herpes as an itty bitty kitty, and at one point, we weren't sure if she was going to be able to keep her eyes.  Luckily, she was able to keep them!  We know that her vision has some impairment, but she still runs and plays with the best of them.
 
Please consider giving Narissa a chance to show you how much she loves to get in your way and climb all over you!
attributes.name: Narissa

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi … my name is Chessie and here are some things you need to know about me!  After you read through my bio, if you think I might be the perfect pup for you, please go to www.allamericanmuttrescue.org/forms and complete your adoption application online.

Blessed be the person who takes in and loves an old dog … For their time with us is more important than our time with them.

I AM A SUPER SENIOR!

I am a big sweet lovebug of a girl who just loves to be loved.  I may be a senior, but I still have lots of love to give.  All I need now is a family of my very own to share the rest of my life with.  I will be sooooo good … and I’ll do everything I can to bring joy to your life.  I’d love to have someone who would take time every day to scratch my ears and rub my belly.  That makes me very happy. I have nice house manners and I am calm enough to be a good companion.  Just tell me what you want to do! Oh ... I would really love to be an only child.  I get along fine with all my foster friends that I have known for a while, but sometimes I don't meet new dogs well.

I’m not too pushy demanding attention, but I really want to stay close to where you are.  If you tell me where you want me to be, I’ll do my best to try to stay there.  Here at my foster home I don’t have to ‘ask’ to go outside to potty because we get to go out in playgroups several times every day, but I know that’s where I’m supposed to go.  I will even stay in a crate for a short time if you ask me to, even though it’s not my favorite place to be.

I don’t mind being leash walked, but I would LOVE to have a fenced yard to explore and sunbathe in.  It will keep me safe because I do have a bad habit of wandering off. My size sort of scares people sometimes, so my search for friends does not always make other people happy.

My Foster Mom says I’m sorta smart.  I do know ‘sit’ and most of the time I will come when she calls me (unless I’m busy doing something else!)  I sorta like to ride in the car.  I don’t get to do it very often, but I think I could really learn to like it as long as I could be with my people.

So … here are some other important things about me … I weigh about 55 lbs, I am spayed, up-to-date on my shots, and I am microchipped.

I do come with papers … Adoption Papers … the best kind.  And my adoption fee is $75.

Note from the AAMR Adoption Committee:  We are an all-volunteer group, so please be patient and understand that it takes an average of 7-14 days to process the applications including reference checks, follow-up questions and home visits.  You can expedite the process by providing accurate email addresses for all your references.  Time to make phone calls is limited and we often have multiple applications in process.  We make every effort to move through them as quickly as possible.

When your application is approved, we will schedule a meet-and-greet and home visit to see if Chessie picks you too.

If it seems that the adoption will be a good match for all, there is an adoption fee, and an adoption contract to be signed. More questions …. email them to weluvpups@hotmail.com

attributes.descriptionHtml:
There isn't enough space on this page to say all the wonderful things about Mr. Jackson Browne!  Jackson would be the most wonderful addition to any home without children and with people who take charge!  You see, Mr. Browne can sometimes be over protective of his family, especially children.  He guards the house and his people that he loves so he needs some direction and a strong leader.  That being said, he has a personality unlike any other pup. He's sweet, playful, silly, loving, and knows when to RELAX!! He's a great cuddler and will curl up next to you, even in the smallest of spaces.  He loves his belly rubs, so be prepared when he stretches out his paws to you!

Jackson also loves to go on walks and adventures and ESPECIALLY loves the water!! He pulls slightly on the leash, but he is great in the car.  Once Jackson meets you, he LOVES you, but it does take time. He is generally good with meeting dogs and people outside on the leash, but sometimes he gets nervous so make sure to properly introduce him first!  Again, Jackson is friendly with most dogs, but can be dog selective.

Jackson is housetrained, knows basic commands, and listens very well. Jackson can be trained easily. He is the most lovable, most precious dog and he will love you completely.

If you'd like to meet Jackson, please fill out an application today, he's sure to put a smile on your face!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi! I am Dexter! Sometimes I am called Dex, sometimes I only answer to Mr. Handsome. I am a cuddly, fun guy who has recovered from paralysis. I had a back injury, likely due to genetics, and I had the surgery to fix it. Due to my back, I should not do stairs. After I rehabbed, I can walk again although I am wobbly and have some bathroom accidents when I don't make it to the doggie door in time. I love to rip apart my stuffed toys and hang with the other foster dogs. I am quiet and easy going. My favorite place to hang out is in the kitchen because that is where the snacks live. Meeting new people is no problem for me because I am friendly and charming. Having someone home with me all the time would be a dream come true, but I can certainly nap while you go to work if that means more snacks and toys, but I will need attention and love when you come home. I enjoy the company of other dogs and pretty much ignore the cat.

I have a secret superpower!  Go look at my video and you can see that I know how to arrange my own covers and tuck myself in to bed.  It took my foster mom a while but she finally got it on video.  I know, pretty cool if I say so myself.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Softest, sweetest little mouse

Don't mistake little Maxine for a big mouse, she's the cuddliest cutest little cat you've seen in a long time. She loves to peer at you from tall places, and when you notice her, oh, the little kisses, then the falling over on her side for belly rubs!

Maxine was rescued from a colony of cats living in a trailer park. The cats were in such danger, many kittens had been torn apart by dogs, adults were driven out into the streets, some starved to death. A kindly man found Maxine hiding her kittens beneath a house and took the little famly in. He kept the kittens, but needed to rehome Maxine. Having spent all her life hiding, you'd think she would be too shy to come out, but right away the purring started.

Maxine loves to be stroked, petted and brushed. She loves to lie next to you, cuddled in the crook of your arm, having her belly rubbed. She's so quiet and sweet, you could forget she's there except for the tiny little meows when she wants to remind you to cuddle.

Maxine is technically a calico, a dilute or pastel calico, but her her lovely coat of many colors shows  dove gray, fawn, pale, pale beige, and a touch of silver. She's oh so pretty.

If you'd like to know more about this lovely and shy lady, email foster dad directly at haroldw1@sbcglobal.net and if you'd like to meet her, go to her webpage at www.happycatadoptions.org and fill out an online application. She's little, she's lovely, and she'll light up with love!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Rough, tough mama!

Rose, the red tabby mom who lived under the ATM in the parking lot of the local bar, has seen it all. People have come and gone, people were either kind or mean, but Rose found herself a little bush, a scrap of loading dock, and a way up inside the post of an AM machine.

When the kittens came, as you knew they would, didn't you, little bitty Rose, scrappy and tough, kept them safe. In fact, those kittens would still be hidden by their mom, had it not been for a torrential downpour that drove them out of their little ATM hideout and into the rocks beneath.

A Happy Cat Adoptions foster was pulling up to the ATM when he saw the little miserable faces under the bushes, and after a four-hour struggle to get all the kittens (Rose went into the trap with little fuss), the tiny family was ensconced in a warm, dry cage with loads of food.

Rose finally had the opportunity to be a kitten herself, for the first time.   Once safely in a foster home, she learned to romp and play and wrestle and run as all kittens like to do. She's a "real cat" now, her foster dad says. 

Rose is hoping for a loving family and a home of her own, one where she will be cherished for all of her life.   She is a very happy girl who really likes other cats and LOVES people.  Adoption to a home with another cat would be perfect for this sweet girl 

To find out more about her, email her foster dad directly at haroldw1@sbcglobal.net or to meet her, go to her webpage at www.happycatadoptions.org and fill out the online adoption form.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
The website is updated daily

Macy is spayed, tested negative for felv/fiv and current on vaccines, born sometime Nov 2009.

Macy is longing for her own human!  She was found one winter in the backyard of a Northeast Philadelphia house, begging for food.  She's been in foster care ever since, and cannot understand why she isn't the center of everyone's attention.

Macy would prefer to be an only cat, and possibly an only pet.  She truly wants a person of her own, who she doesn't need to share.  When her foster mom goes into her room to scoop and clean, Macy rolls on the tops of her feet, demanding attention.  She loves to be brushed and held and fussed over.  Her foster mom feels that once she has her forever home, she'll follow her person from room to room, and sleep either in bed with them, or very close by.  Pretty much, she will just worship her person.

Take a good look at her pictures, she has a sweet, pink nose, and some beautiful tabby calico patches.  Don't let her expression in her photos fool you - she's really a happy cat!  It's just that the tabby patch and eye liner on her one eye make her look like she glares.  Nothing could be further from the truth.  She's an affectionate, sweetheart who lives for attention.

If interested in Macy please fill an application out at www.nar.rescuegroups.org

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Our Website is updated daily

Lola is UTD on vaccines, spayed and tested negative for FIV/FeLV. EDOB is Sept. 1, 2010.

Lola's a sweet, very affectionate little girl who may not be the cat for the first time cat owner.  While she will shower you with affection, and loves to be with you and cuddle, she is a bit feisty.  She loves to play, get brushed, and clipping nails is not a problem.  You just need to be able to read her correctly.  

See, she learned to play rough with humans as a kitten, and now she doesn't know that we don't enjoy that.  Verbal correction works just fine, and if you catch her right before, the correction works.  Unlike the spoiled brat who nips when something is displeasing - Lola nips to show she's having fun, or to show affection when she gets overstimulated by a situation.  Her foster mom is working on her manners.  

This beautiful, silky soft torbi is very clean with her litter-box, but does like to dig a bit.  To prove that she's clean, she washes her feet in her water bowl - cute!  After a good round of playing, she loves to fall asleep in your arms - purring the whole time.  She purrs and will greet you at the door - but will also flop on the floor in front of you while you're walking.  You'll have to watch your step, as she doesn't understand it's not your fault if she gets stepped on.

Lola most likely will need to be an only pet.  She won't let the dog of the house into the room she lives in.  She's not happy with the other cats, either.  She's a bit curious about them, but if they get too close to the door, she hisses terribly and they back away.

If you're interested in adopting Lola, please fill out an application at www.nar.rescuegroups.org.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Are you looking for a handsome companion? Meet Bo! He is an adorable 10 year old 74 pound, dalmation/pitbull/pointer mix great with other dogs, smaller and his own size and will only chase a cat if its running (he thinks it wants to play) He loves to chase balls at the beach, the park, the yard...anywhere you want to throw it! He knows verbal and hand commands for sit, wait, down, back, off, in, and outside. He is also crate trained and will go in when asked. He absolutely loves KONG toys and is such a playful boy. Bo loves to travel and does well in the car. He likes camping, the beach, and camping at the beach. Due to his large size, he needs a strong pack leader who will follow through with his training and provide him with a stable and loving environment. Also due to his size, he would do best in a home with older, respectful children.

If you are interested in adopting, please visit the I.C.A.R.E. Dog Rescue website and complete an adoption application: www.icaredogrescue.org/ready-to-adopt

Adoption fee includes: spay/neuter • shots up to date • micro-chip • fecal and vet check

attributes.descriptionHtml: Tesha is a good dog but has a few issues.  Tesha is incontinent and is unable to control her bladder. She's about 3 years old and is a basset hound breed.  She can be aggressive with any other animals so it is best that she be in a home as an only animal in the home. She is blind in one and has chronic skin issues that will need attention daily. She can be very loving with certain individuals but does not like strange females as all. She has a fun black white and brown spotted coat. Her little tail always wags when she is happy.  She is a very loud barker but is able to be calm in the mornings but can bark at night a lot. She has been fixed and is up to date on all vaccines.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
DOB: January 2011

Breed/Coloring: Catahoula Leopard Dog Mix

Size: Brenna weighs about 55lbs and is full grown

History: Brenna was dumped at a Ventura shelter. We rescued her from there right before they would have been euthanized. 

Personality: Brenna is very sweet with people but not a big fan of other dogs. She can be very affectionate and is SUPER willing to please people - but is also a bit shy. She is very smart and would do well with proper training and TLC.

Training: Brenna has not really had much opportunity to be trained because we suspect she has been kenneled or in a yard most of her life. She will need work on housebreaking, basic obedience, and leash. We strongly recommend starting her off with crate training and an in-home consultation with a trainer. As smart as she is, we don't think that it will take her long to become a fantastic member of any household.

Would Do Best: Brenna would do best as an only-dog in a home with a large yard space. She needs a family that will spend time on her training and that has some experience with training a larger treeing dog. Please read about her breed and their needs here:  http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/catahoula.htm

Cats, Dogs and Kids: Brenna cannot be with cats or other dogs because of her breed and prey drive. She would be okay with teenagers that are patient and calm, but we do not recommend her for young children or noisy/busy homes.

VET RECORD: All of our dogs are currently vaccinated, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

AVAILABILITY: This dog is available for adoption now and is being fostered or kenneled in the San Fernando Valley area. Please email us and we will send you an adoption application. Local adoptions only (we do not ship dogs).

Visit our website: http://www.foreverhomepetrescue.org/

Breed/Coloring: Terrier Mix; brown/black

Size: Layla weighs about 20lbs and is full grown

History: Layla was left tied to the mailbox at a rescue kennel in the summertime and almost died because of the heat. She has lived at the kennel ever since then and would love to have a home of her own.

Personality: Layla is very sweet but a bit shy.  She likes to be the Alpha doggie with other dogs, but is timid with people. Once she has a "normal" life we know she will blossom into a super friendly girl.

Training: Layla has been in a kennel environment so she will need work on her housebreaking - she would like access to yard space.

Would Do Best: Layla would do best with in an adult only home with someone who can give her the love and time she deserves.

Cats, Dogs and Kids:  Layla is great with other dogs as long as she can be in charge... she likes calmer, male dogs best. She is great with cats but we don't think she would do well with young children.

attributes.descriptionHtml: My name is Buttons and I'm approximately 13 years old. I was abandoned by my owners when I was about 1 year old in 2008.  I have been living at the BCHS shelter since that time.  I am a little shy at first.  Once I get comfortable with new people and situations I am easy going and affectionate.   I live in a community room with other cats and get along with them.  I am on food for urinary health because I did have a UTI in 2013.  I have been diagnosed with IBD (Inflammatory Bowel Disease).  The condition if gone untreated can cause vomiting and/or diarrhea.  I am on a regimen of a low dose of prednisone every other day and I get a Vitamin B-12 shot every 2 weeks.  With this regimen of treatment I do very well. The current treatment plan is a lifetime plan for me.  My health issues do not keep me from playing with toys and some of the other cats in my community room.  I would really like to have a home of my own where I can get all the love and attention I deserve.  I am available for immediate adoption. I am spayed, UTD on vaccinations, tested for FeLV/FIV, treated for internal and external parasites and micro chipped. My adoption fee is by donation. If you are interested in adopting me please complete an Adoption Profile in person or on-line at www.bondcohs.petfinder.com. Email the completed profile to the address provided.  A copy of our policy regarding warranties, refunds, or returns is available upon request..

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Gideon is a 7 year old cuddly boy in search of a good home. He is neutered and up to date on all vaccines, flea and heartworm preventative medication. He is great with children - lives with a 2 year old and a 3 year old and is incredibly patient with their attention. He loves attention and cuddles and regularly sits on people's laps if they are on the floor. He is housebroken. He is not currently crate trained but we are working on it. 
 
Gideon is a protector with high anxiety. He goes on high alert when out with his people on walks or car rides. He has been on anxiety medication for 3 years and has some destructive habits when separated from his people. A good home for Gideon would require someone with the patience and knowledge to help




 him through his anxiety. 
 
He needs a home with a yard, preferably fenced (high fence - he can jump!) so he can run and roam. He is prey driven and has caught rabbits, snakes and turtles (and tried to catch squirrels and birds). He does well with other dogs when properly introduced and attends doggy daycare occasionally. He was raised with another lab for the first few years of his life and LOVED her - I think he misses having a doggy friend but needs one that is not going to challenge his alpha spot or they may not get along. He has never been around a cat but I would worry about the prey drive in that situation.
attributes.name: Gideon

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, my name is Kira, I have been at the Olive Branch waiting for my perfect home. I have had a bit of a shaky past with men, so I need a female only home. I would rather not live with children or other animals. I am a special needs girl, I have arthritis that occcasionally gives me twinges, and a heart condition that is being helped with medication. Even at my age, I'm still a pretty active girl. I have been spayed, my vaccinations are al current, and tested negative for heart worm and Lyme Disease. I am also current with my worming, flea and tick preventives, and my heart worm preventive- Interceptor Plus. If you have a place in your life and heart for me, fill out the adoption application on the left of this website.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Lucas is available through our Homebuddies program. He is located at our Temple, Ga adoption center. 

Lucas will require a single family home and a fence suitable for free run exercise for an active dog.  An apartment, condo or congested home setting would be very stressful for Lucas.  He will require an adopter willing to be very careful with him as he could be a flight risk if scared and adopter is not diligent with gates, doors and training.  He will also require patience on the part of his adopter and any visitors because he is very timid upon meeting new people.  He has come a long way since arriving at our shelter.  We are pleased with his progress and want to give him the best chance possible to succeed going forward.

Size: 66 pounds 

DOB: 2009 

Health: Healthy 

Behavior: playful, goofy 

Playfulness: can be, loves to run around

Affectionate: Yes  

Calm: Mostly 

High Energy: Low  

Dog Friendly: Yes, with females 

Cat Friendly: No   

Toddler/Baby Appropriate: No

Child Appropriate: Older with supervision  

Good for first time dog owners: No 

Fetches: Yes 

Swims: unknown   

Other: Shy to new people and men. 

Hi! I'm Lucas.  When I first got here, I came down with parvo and was very, very sick for a while.  It got even worse when I got a respiratory infection while I was trying to fight the parvo. Everyone was shocked when I finally got to go home after almost two weeks.  But I made it! I'm a fighter and just a wonderful dog with a big heart.  And I'm pretty darn good-looking, too!  

I'm surprised I haven't been adopted yet because I feel like I'm a really great dog that will make a wonderful buddy for almost anyone!  I love to run and play and have lots of great friends here, including my girlfriend Blossom.  I'm really well-behaved.  I listen well and I'm even allowed outside the fence to go swimming at our lake here. 

I'm really athletic and I can jump a 4' fence so it's safest for me if you have a 6' fence or don't leave me outside alone.  I would love to be with an active person or family who can keep me busy retrieving, swimming, running or hiking.  But I'm also cuddly and affectionate, so I need that too.

Do you think you can give me the home I deserve? I have been at IWAG for 10+ years! I would love to spend the rest of my days exploring your yard and cuddling with you! If you are interested in me, fill out an application at IWAG.org!

Willow's story:

Willow (known as "Will" to his friends) came to us as a checkout from a local kill shelter when he was just two weeks old.  Fearing that he was too little to have a fair shot in our shelter, he was fostered in the home of our Executive Director for nearly three months.

In his time with us, he has grown and thrived! He will make a great member of a family.

Willow is a very sweet boy who gets along well with kid and with other cats.  The distinctive-looking markings on his head make him look like he's wearing a toupee! 

Are you the perfect forever home for Willow?

Approximate date of birth: 4/14/2011

Gender: M

OK with kids: Yes

attributes.descriptionHtml: Susie is a sweetie pie for sure. She can start off a bit shy but her natural curiosity usually takes over and has her coming to say “HI” in her gentle and quiet way. Once she warms up to you there’s no holding back this girl’s affectionate side. She will likely follow you around the room to be petted and to bestow loving nuzzles. There is a good chance Susie will make a great cuddle bug in a home setting. Susie’s gorgeous tiger striped coat and expressive face add to her charming personality giving this girl a winning appeal. She gets along well with her kitty roommates and would do well in a multi-cat home. She will do best in a quiet, laid-back environment where catnaps and cuddles are required daily activities. Susie is a sure bet for someone looking for a sweet, gentle and lovable addition to their lives. She is spayed, vaccinated, tested neg. for FeLuk/FIV and micro-chipped. Call Friends of Michigan Animals Rescue at 734 461-9458 or visit our website fmar1.org for more information.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Max is a big mush of a dog that enjoys the attention of people and smiles from ear to ear when you talk to him. He loves going for a ride in the car and makes the best co-pilot, ever!! Max the Mush has been at the kennel for almost 8 years on and off! It is truly heartbreaking. Max is soo loving and loyal!! He is great in the car, loves walks, his toys, and is food motivated!

Max is approximately 11.5 years old, but he acts much younger. The high stress environment of the kennel is no place for him to live out the rest of his life. He has not had very many opportunities to interact with other dogs so he would do best in a single pet house unless we could find the perfect match of a doggie sibling. Max has met a volunteer's dog and did well with her; even showing signs of wanting to play. However, he has never lived with one, so that might be too stressful of a change for him. He has not reacted well to cats, so we are firm with the no felines rule. 

The ideal home for Max would be quiet without many visitors. He would do best with older, respectful kids as he gives big, rough kisses that may startle or knock over a younger child. Max would also need someone who is willing to take it slowly with him and willing to meet him several times before bringing him home. He is such a gem that continuously gets overlooked. He has so much love to give, we promise you will not need anything else if you have Max. He always has the biggest smile on his face, too. Please consider Max!

If you're willing to take a chance on Max, you will be rewarded with a loyal & trusting friend. Please consider giving Max a home to live out his golden years!

Max won the heart of a family and they have very kindly sponsored Max's adoption fee!!!

Dempsey was returned after 9 years due to his owner moving into assisted living. He is now 11 yrs old and finds himself looking for a home, once again, to finish out his golden years. Dempsey is still very young at heart and enjoys long walks. He is housetrained and does not get into anything that does not belong to him. He wants nothing more than to be around others, whether you are running around the yard, doing chores around the house, or catching a post work nap. He is a great companion for other dogs but does need to be fed separately. He is able to jump 4 ft chainlink fences so he will need to be on a tie out or leash at all times or have a privacy fence. Dempsey is up to date on his vaccinations and ready to start meeting new people. Please come meet this sweet boy, you won’t regret it.

If you would like to meet or adopt Dempsey please fill out an online application. Questions to cbrookszy@yahoo.com.

Am looking to relocate to a forever home, and hoping you will stop by to see me in the next few weekends at PetSmart.  Remember - I'll bring you lots of good karma!!!

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, I’m Gretzky. My brother and I spent our first 3 months on the streets and when we came to the SBACC, we were very scared and very wild. Everyone was really nice to us and we calmed down, but remained shy and timid cats. My brother became a little more outgoing with time and was adopted a long time ago. I’m a very handsome tabby boy who is still shy, but I now enjoy petting from people I know, and I love to play with the mouse on a wire toy!  I need a quiet home with a cat savvy Mom or Dad who will give me plenty of time to adjust to a new home.  Although I live with other cats at the shelter, I think I might be fine as an only cat, as long as I have people to pay attention to me!

If you think you would like to meet me or adopt me please fI'll out an online application.

Please send questions to cbrookszy@yahoo.com

attributes.descriptionHtml: Dillon is a handsome senior bulldog mix with the cutest underbite ever!  He is housebroken, non destructive when left alone, walks fantastically on leash and absolutely loves car rides!  He also loves to run around and play fetch!  He is good with dogs but needs to learn some manners while playing with them.  He is a little sensitive to being petted at first but once you form that bond with him he just loves to cuddle (watch out he snores and hogs the bed!).  He would do best in a quiet home with DOG SAVVY adults with minimal visitors (or be willing to put him away when having visitors which he doesn’t mind).  Please give this boy a chance and let him live his senior years in a home.
attributes.name: Dillon Spalding

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Precious boy with loving heart seeks a home of his own!

Scamp lcouldn't be cuter. He's a little lover with a bunch of personality. His ears say it all. "What's going on" and the ears go back. "Love you" and the ears come up. He loves high places, jingly toys, and pets.

Scamp is the cat raised by possums. His foster family found him as a tiny kitten, living behind their barn with a few possum adolescents. He was fending for himself and if you'd seen his scruffy fur, dirty face, and bad manners, you wouldn't recognize him. Now his fur is sleek, he has the physique of a romance novel cover cat, and the personality of a star.

Scamp needs a home, maybe with some children, maybe not, to give him the love and cuddles and ear scritchies he deserves.  He's already discovered that the eats never end once you've been rescued!

To meet this doll face baby, go to his webpage at www.happycatadoptions.org and click the adoption link under his photo to fill out the easy online application. His foster family would be glad to arrange a meeting.

Scamp's adoption fee of $125 is used to rescue more possum babies. Er...kitties.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Halo was born 12/5/2011.  She is a beautiful Tortoiseshell with Amber eyes.

Halo was found giving birth in the rain on top of a wooden crate.  A wonderful man rescued her and the 5 babies bringing them inside, giving them blankets, food and water.  He then called animal control only to be horrified when they told him "yes, bring them in, we can euthanize them."  He replied with "Oh yes, let's do that.  The babies are only 4 hours old."

Halo who was a dumped pregnant cat has only 4 babies left as one died shortly after birth.  She has been an absolutely wonderful mother, but sadly mothers rarely get adopted as everyone wants a kitten.

Halo is not a lap cat but if she had a home where there was a lot of love and patience, I am sure she would eventually let you touch her.  Halo is not aggressive.  She is just scared because people in her past haven't been exactly very nice to her.

Please help us find a great home for Halo.  She has truly been an Angel with all that she has had to endure so early in life!  Halo plays well with other kitties but would be a PERFECT "only cat".

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Sally is a little over 9 years old as of April, 2021 and weighs around 69 pounds. This gal has a very affectionate and loving personality with her person. She loves to hug and cuddle and is great in the house. She is loyal and protective of her owner. She just needs to be introduced to new people and then there is no problem as long as mom and dad says it's ok, she's great. Sally does not like other dogs and would do best as the only dog in the home. However, we do have a laid back male here named Little Red that she gets along great with. She is crate trained, house trained and walks on a leash. She loves, loves to go for walks and still has some energy even at her age. Sally also loves to curl up with her person in bed and get lots of belly rubs. She has been around children with no issues either. She loves, loves, loves her people or person. She would be great with a single person or couple that want an alert gal to watch over them and to get lots of cuddles. Sally is spayed, heartworm negative and current on shots, heartworm and flea prevention. 

If you are interested in visiting or adopting, please submit our application at RichardsonRescue.org. Sally does qualify for the Senior for Seniors Program. All visits require an approved application and are by APPOINTMENT ONLY.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Spook is available through our Homebuddies program! He is located at our Temple, Ga adoption center. 

DOB: 2010

Health: Healthy 

Behavior: playful and affectionate 

Playfulness: Very  

Affectionate: VERY, Loves giving hugs

Calm: Can be 

High Energy: Low/Medium  

Dog Friendly: Yes

Cat Friendly: No

Toddler/Baby Appropriate: No

Child Appropriate: No  

Good for first time dog owners: Yes, be advised that he does not like men

Fetches: No  

Swims: No   

Other: Can be reserved at first until he gets to know you. Gives GREAT hugs, very sweet and loving. Loves women. 

Hi!  I'm Spook.  Sometimes they call me Pookie, Spooky, Pookin, anything really! I just want to be called "yours"!  I came with the name Spook because I used to be scared of everything... And for good reason!  I got a pretty rough start.  I came from a horrible shelter, which was bad enough.  But then something got stuck in my lungs when the doctor's were neutering me. Then my tail got chopped off in a door where I was staying. The group that was keeping me got in big trouble and me and all the other dogs had to leave.  I was so happy when I was brought here! IWAG has showed me what loves means for the past 8 years, and I'm ready to show my forever family how good of a boy I am! Please let me spend the rest of my years in a home, cuddled up with you on the couch!

I still can be nervous around other men but I am getting much better! I love to give you hugs and protect you and the entire family.  I will be the sweetest dog you will ever meet! If you are interested in me, fill out an application at IWAG.org.
attributes.name: Spook

attributes.descriptionHtml:
This beautiful, intelligent girl is Merry.  Merry loves to go!  She loves to ride in the car and run on the beach.   She loves tennis balls and tug-a-war.    Merry and the rest of her siblings play a fun game of hide and seek or chase. She is very affectionate and loves to cuddle.

Merry will need a loving hand.   She is a loving, intelligent animal who needs a lot of stimulus.  

Merry will do well in a house with older children and at least 1 other dog. 

Merry is kennel trained - 4-5 hour stretches she sleeps through the night - averaging 6 -7 hours.  Merry has storm and noise anxiety and will destroy a crate in a storm or with fireworks.

Merry is house broken, although we use a doggy door so she has full access to house and yard.

Merry is a blood donor for Blue Pearl in Houston.

Please contact app@aarfhouston.org for more information about this dog or to schedule a meet and greet. You can apply online by clicking on Application . Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events. Thank you for considering a rescue!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Frankie one big hunk of love.   He is active!  Loves to run and play outside with his siblings.   Loves tennis balls and tug-a-war.   

Frankie is a cuddle bug who has been spoiled rotten and loves to sleep on the bed snuggling close. 

He is very attentive and bright. Frankie is very loving and responds to love and affection and positive reinforcement.

Frankie is eager to please - loves being with his family.  He is  a loving gentle dog.    He knows basic command.  Wiggles his little behind when called, knows Sit,  potty, bed, and of course treat.   He understands "Share".. but sometimes decides to ignore that command!     He is a favorite in the household!

Frankie will do well in a house with older children and at least 1 other dog his energy level.  Frank doesn't tolerate puppy energy well.  Not recommended for families with children under 8.  

Frankie does NOT Kennel, but is also not destructive.  Frankie is house broken and has full access to house and yard through a doggie door.

Please contact app@aarfhouston.org for more information about this dog or to schedule a meet and greet. You can apply online by clicking on Application . Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events. Thank you for considering a rescue!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Freddie is your "ride-a-long guy".   He is happiest when he can run and explore.   If that is with you  - so much better!   A ride in the car, a run on the beach, a swim - Freddie is your guy. 

Loves tennis balls and tug-a-war - Hide and Seek.   Fred loves to ride shotgun when we go for frequent car trips.    He is a momma's boy and talks until you pay attention to him.  

He is docile, very attentive and bright.  He is gentle and would rather play with the older kids or other dogs in the house than with his rough and tumble siblings.   Freddie loves to cuddle and wants to cuddle before he goes to sleep. 

Freddie needs a firm, loving hand and consistent training.   Eager to please - loves being with his family.   He is a loving, intelligent animal who needs a lot of stimulus.    Freddie talks when he wants something and wiggles his little behind when called. He knows basic commands:  Sit potty, bed, and of course treat.   He understands "Share". but sometimes decides to ignore that command! 

Freddie will do well in a house with older children and at least 1 other dog.  He is bonded to his sister Merry.  He will seek her company and sometimes sleeps with her in her crate.

 Fred's mom was a Boxer/SharPei and we think dad may have been lab.

  NOT RECOMMENDED FOR FAMILIES WITH SMALL CHILDREN.

Freddie may not be the most beautiful of the litter, but his personality beats them all.   He definitely needs more affection and attention than the rest, but you are truly rewarded with the love and affection 10 times over.   


Please contact app@aarfhouston.org for more information about this dog or to schedule a meet and greet. You can apply online by clicking on Application . Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events. Thank you for considering a rescue!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hello there, my name is Petey :) Clearly you can see that I am just a handsome boy! I was taken into Eleventh Hour when my recent owners could no longer care for me. Since coming to EHR I have met many wonderful people. My foster who takes me home says I am housebroken, know all my basic commands (and a few bonus extras) 

UPDATE FROM CURRENT HOME:

In the time we have had him Petey has improved his understanding of basic commands (sit, stay, down) as well as learned some new ones. We have been working on "Leave it" and "Drop it" and he has been responding well. We also are able to get him to wait for his food until we give the "OK" and are able to stop him eating with "leave it." We have not noticed any type of food aggression with him, he takes treats very nicely and won't take a treat until we say "OK".


Petey is very good in the crate. When we first got him we tried to leave him in the house all day and he had an accident on the carpet EVERY day. We tried baby gates and barriers and he always jumped them. We figured it was a separation anxiety reaction from him. Since we started using the crate he has not had one accident and comes and goes from it on his own when the door is open. It definitely keeps him calm when we are out of the house. We do have him sleep in it at night as well, but he of course would love to just be in bed with us all night if he could. He is such a snuggler, still very affectionate and just wanting to be by us all the time.

We definitely feel like he needs to be an only dog in a family with no children and who wouldn't have him interact with small animals or children. He definitely needs a lot of attention and love. We think he would love to run around and play in a high fenced yard.
He also now responds to the name Dexter.

Meet big Midnight, a big dog, who's really a marshmellow inside. Midnight is fiercely loyal to his family and sweet a companion. He thinks he's a small lapdog and loves to snuggle with his human. He loves car rides and going anywhere he can be near his human.

Midnight is great with his female furry foster sisters and with the older children in the home. He would not be good with another territorial male or cats. Nor should he be in a home with small children  just because of his size - he may get excited and accidently knock them down or step on them. Despite his large size, Midnight loves to play and has a lot of energy. 

Midnight is housebroken and crate trained. He's very well behaved in the house and is not a trouble maker at all. His adoption fee is $125.  For more information, please call 662-342-9448; email us via info@desotoanimalrescue.org or submit a pre-adoption application here:  http://desotoanimalrescue.org/dog-adoption-application.html

attributes.descriptionHtml:
BEAR NEEDS TO BE PLACED IN A HOME WITHOUT CHILDREN AND NEEDS AN ADVANCED DOG SAVVY HUMAN, HE ALSO REQUIRES A FENCED YARD (5 FOOT OR HIGHER)

Bear....aka "Air Bear"

Bear is a 8 1/2 year old smooth coat male Border Collie mix being fostered in Plymouth, Indiana

This dog can fly through the air....typically after a tennis ball ;)
Bear is approaching 8 years of age but hasn't really slowed down over the years.... he is still willing to play fetch ALL day if I'd let him. Bear is good with other dogs, however he can be a bit of a target for dogs to pick on.... he hates confrontation with other dogs and will usually bark and sort of scream a bit to ask them to give him some space. He is not a dog that wants to fight with other dogs....he wants to flee. He currently lives in my home with 10 other dogs and is great! He will chase kitties for fun but has never tried to hurt them. He is suspicious of people he doesn't know and will avoid them when given the choice....however he will play ball with ANYONE!! Once he is familiar and comfortable with someone he is great. I have zero issues with handling him for grooming, nail trimming, etc. He does have to be muzzled for vet visits as he doesn't want strangers invading his personal space. I typically muzzle and handle him for his vet visits so that he is not stressed about someone doing it.
He has taken a few Agility classes and has worked with a few different people in those classes and works well with other people in a training setting. He wouldn't take much more work to have ready for Novice Agility classes. He would make a nice performance partner for a dog savvy handler. One that understood that fearful dogs need space and to feel safe before they can be expected to perform in unfamiliar environments. Bear has been overlooked for years due to his quirks which I can understand but he is just a super easy dog to live with in my country setting. I haven't given up hope that he may have a home of his own one day (4/2020)


Bear will need a family who will be patient with him as he is slow to warm up to new people and places.  Please contact stephodellfcr@hotmail.com if you have any questions about Bear.  You can complete an application to adopt Bear or any of the dogs on our website at www.comebyebcrescue.org.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Fabulous Freddy Paterson!  Freddy is a senior pit mix who has the cutest underbite you’ll ever see.  He was rescued by Eleventh Hour from an abandoned basement at 6 months old.  Then, Freddy went into a home for about 3 years.  Unfortunately, his owner became too ill to care for him and he was brought back to the shelter - he hasn’t had another home since.  Freddy is just an incredibly sweet, fun and loyal guy!  He absolutely LOVES car ride adventures and squeaky toys.  But, his ultimate favorite thing to do is snuggle as close as he possibly can!  Freddy takes just a little time to warm up to new people but once he does, snuggles and kisses will be available every day!   He would do best in a quiet home with just a couple or a single person (no kids) who is willing to put him away when they have visitors - Freddy becomes protective of his person/people.  He would prefer to be the only pet so he can get all the attention, which he deserves.  Freddy is housebroken and doesn’t make a peep in the house unless he hears someone outside.  He is the true definition of mans best friend and will make you feel so loved and happy.  

 

Check out my video on my profile to prove how amazing of a cuddler I am!

 

If you are interested in meeting Freddy please fill out the adoption application for Eleventh Hour Rescue.
attributes.name: Freddy Paterson

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Every cat in the world loves him! People too...

Roaming the neighborhood looking for scraps was not the life this brown spotted tabby boy had imagined when he was a kitten. As a kitten, someone loved him; someone petted him; someone cuddled him. We know that because even though he was fearful and shy when he arrived at his foster home as a stray, the minute he was trapped and brought inside to be evaluated, the purrs started. And they have never stopped.

That brown tabby boy became Tibet, a big spotty boy with a sleek coat and a mellow disposition. As new kitties arrive at his foster home, he rushes to meet them and enfold them in his arms. When potential adopters come to meet the other kitties, Tibet comes to hop onto a lap and ask, "Hey, are you here for me?"

He knew what a loving home was; he knows this isn't his furever home. He's having fun, but he needs someone to kiss his head and say, "You're my baby." He wants toys that aren't hand me downs, and he wants a home with another companion animal so he can play and nurture them.

Tibet's brown color is more of a dark gray, and his stripes are so indistinct, he's spotted. His muzzle is creamy colored and his cheeks, because he wasn't fixed until he was an adult, are poofy. He's cute.

More than his looks, Mr. Tibet relies on his winning personality. He loves to cuddle in a lap, loves to sit on the chair by you, or cuddle up when you're lying down. He purrs when you're not feeling good, and he's quiet and mellow. All his friends at his foster home, both people and cats, love him. He's looking for a  home with other cats.

To find out more about this sweet boy, contact his foster dad directly.

To meet this charmer, click the adoption link under his photo from the website: www.happycatadoptions.org. Fill out the online form, and someone will contact you within a few days to arrange a meeting.

Tibet's adoption fee helps to rescue more homeless kitties.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, I'm Lucy. I have the most beautiful glossy black coat. I came to SBACC with my brother, Desi, and we were both very frightened at first. Everyone thought we were feral cats because we did not want to be touched. After a while we both realized that no one at SBACC was going to hurt us, they just wanted to be our friends. Desi started to trust people before I did and he was adopted. I have changed a lot, I love to play, especially with anything on a string. Now, I like it when I am petted but I do not stay still too long, I would rather play - or go back to sleep! I actually think I would do best as an only cat, even though I tolerate my roommates!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
I am a 7 year old Chihuahua/Jack Russell Terrier mix. When I was only a few months old, my owner surrendered me to the pound. I was afraid and too young to be without my mommy. I was quickly taken to the back where they were going to put me to sleep, when an angel from I.C.A.R.E. Dog Rescue intercepted and saved my life! I showed her how grateful I was by showering her with love and kisses. She said I was as sweet as a Twinkie! Since I was taken from my mommy so early, I have had some struggles, but I don't take life for granted. I am a great dog, but sometimes it takes me a while to trust people and I can bet scared. I am not a snuggly dog and much prefer to have my own space and will let you know when I'm seeking affection. I cannot be picked up.  I have a lot of energy and I get along great with other dogs. I would love to go to a home with another dog. I am also great on walks and think they are so much fun! I am ready to live life to the fullest! Can you be my furever family?

If you are interested in adopting, please visit the I.C.A.R.E. Dog Rescue website and complete an adoption application: www.icaredogrescue.org/ready-to-adopt

Adoption fee includes: spay/neuter • shots up to date • micro-chip • fecal and vet check

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Chase is available through our Homebuddies program. He is located at our Temple, Ga adoption center. He likes female dog friends, but needs to meet them first just to make sure.  

DOB: 2011

Health: Healthy 

Behavior: Very active, playful, and loves to fetch  

Playfulness: Very  

Affectionate: Very   

Calm: Not often 

High Energy: Very 

Dog Friendly: Females Only

Cat Friendly: No  

Toddler/Baby Appropriate: No

Child Appropriate: No  

Good for first time dog owner: No 

Fetches: Yes 

Swims: Yes  

Other: Obsessed with toys and fetching. Absolutely loves to swims

Hi! My name is Chase!

I was rescued from a high-kill shelter in Columbus, GA.  I have been here for a long time, 8 years to be exact! I've got tons of energy and love to fetch and swim! I could swim for days. The nice volunteers here take me swimming every week! It's my favorite thing. And I can jump so super high, you'll be impressed with my skills!

I get really excited when I see cars and trucks; I hope it's my new family coming to visit! I like to bark to tell everyone that someone is here, but I'll be quiet when they tell me to, I'm a good listener. They tell me it's ok to be excited, but not TOO excited and I'm trying my best! I'm just a very goofy, chocolate lab! Everyone says they understand why I'm so goofy, come find out for yourself!

I am a heartworm survivor.  I had to be on bedrest for two months. I didn't think I could do it but I did it! Everyone here at IWAG is amazing, but I want my own fur-ever family to live out my glory days with. 

I like to have a girlfriend or two, but I don't like other males dogs much. I don't wanna share the ladies! Come out and visit with me! Let's throw the ball for a while and see where it goes!

To come see me, fill out an application at IWAG.org!

attributes.descriptionHtml: Collette is a very laid-back, sweet girl that likes to lay around and just take in the scenery. She loves to be petted and enjoys playing with toy mice, especially if they are coated in catnip! Collette enjoys good conversation and affection with the people she knows and trusts. But like many cats, she can get nervous in new situations or where there is a lot of activity, so she would do best in a quiet home. Collette doesn't mind other cats, but is not likely to be playful with them, and she is okay with dogs as long as they respect her. Collette is on a special diet and a low dose medication due to past GI issues. Collette is a wonderful senior feline, looking for her own special forever home where she can enjoy her golden years!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Snickers is a handsome boy who is full of so much love to give.  He is very "laid back", gentle and easy going.  When it's time to cuddle up on the sofa to watch TV, Snickers is right there making himself quite comfortable.  Usually laying on one of the pillows!  He becomes very attached to his humans.  Smart, lovable and ready to be spoiled more than he already is.  Very bonded with his brother, Peanut, and they must be adopted together.  Playful, sweet and fun.  He is very sweet and loving.  He has an "old soul" and will always be quietly by your side, ready to give and receive love.  He could easily become your soulmate. 

Snickers has intermittent seizures which 3 vets have determined are ideopathic.  He is on meds to help with that.  Environmental allergies, mostly to grass, are also something this sweetheart deals with causing skin issues. 

Snickers was born at his foster mom's and was adopted out with his brother, Peanut.  They have been together since birth.  Unfortunately, a divorce  tore their family of over a year apart.  They are back with their original foster mom, loving it, being spoiled!  Snickers and his brother Peanut must be adopted together so these sweet boys don't have to deal with being torn apart from each other.  They are each other's best friend and comfort.  You won't be disappointed with these 2 wonderful loving boys! Give them time to adjust, and you'll have the most loving and loyal dogs you could ask for!  For 5 1/2 years they have been each other's strength, comfort and best friend.

Their perfect forever home waits for them, we just know it! Could it be yours?

 

 

Please contact  info@aarfhouston.org for more information about this dog or to schedule a meet and greet. You can apply online by clicking on Application . Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events. Thank you for considering a rescue!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
“A dark eyed beauty with a smile all her own.”

Hi! I’m Ellie, a sweet, affectionate girl who is on a journey to find my forever home.  I was rescued from an abandoned yard and am so excited to have an opportunity to find a family that I can love.

Training and trust have been key on the road to my transformation from orphan to loyal companion. I’m learning how to interact properly with dogs of various sizes, and how to listen to my handler when distractions exist. I know many commands, such as sit, stay, shake, no, come, go potty, down, roll over, and give kisses. I’m house trained, leash trained and crate trained.

I love as much positive attention as possible, (who doesn’t?) and am not certain I want to share your affection with other animals. I like Nylabones, Kong toys and real bones but have a hard time sharing such treats with canine buddies. (I never got any before I was rescued.) A home where I can be the sole shining canine star would be ideal.

I’ve been described as very affectionate, (I love cuddles!), sensitive, and mostly submissive. I can be insecure when it comes to loud noises, such as thunderstorms and fireworks. My future owners will need to be patient and kind, and continue with my training and socialization.

I’m a sweet girl who is longing for a home where I’ll never be left behind again. Can you help me complete my journey and make my dreams of a loving home come true?

For more information or questions, email Tim at tmb611@msn.com.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Poor Madison is heartbroken.  She was adopted 8 years ago and now finds herself needing a new home.  Her owners are moving and decided she can not go with them.  Last Chance Animal Rescue is committed to our animals and since we would not want her to go to a shelter , we took her back into our foster program.  We are lucky to have wonderful fosters to care for her. Madison is a senior dog that just wants someone to play with and love her.   She is house trained, loves to fetch and is very sweet.  She lived with other dogs but seems to be dog selective at this time.   This may be due to  the fact that she is probably very confused as to why her family left her.  If you are looking for a loving, older, but playful companion , Madison would be happy to fill that role.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
***********SPECIAL NEEDS - HAS ONLY ONE EYE

DOB: January 1, 2013

BREED/COLORING: Labrador MIX, black with white paws 

SIZE: Jacklyn weighs about 50lbs fully grown. 

HISTORY: Jacklyn was witnessed being dumped out of a car in a warehouse district in South Central LA on a weekend when nobody was around. Thankfully the witness happens to be a rescuer. 

PERSONALITY: Jacklyn is SUPER affectionate and sweet. She has lots of energy and loves attention. 

TRAINING: Jacklyn will need leash training and at least a basic obedience course. She is already doing FANTASTIC with crate training and housebreaking. She is extremely smart. 

WOULD DO BEST:  Jacklyn would do best in a home with a family that will spend lots of time loving her, playing with her, and training her. She requires a yard. Because she only has one eye, she is not a dog that can go off-leash hiking and must be kept on leash out in public at all times.

CATS/DOGS/KIDS: Jacklyn is good with other big dogs that are not alpha. She is great with children that can handle her size/energy. She is not recommended for homes with cats. 

VET RECORD: All of our dogs are currently vaccinated, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.  

AVAILABILITY: This dog is available for adoption now and is being fostered or kenneled in the San Fernando Valley area. Please email us and we will send you an adoption application. Local adoptions only - we do not ship dogs.

Visit our website:  http://www.foreverhomepetrescue.org/

attributes.descriptionHtml:
HEY!  I've been on this site for quite awhile.  So, I'm gonna put my cards on the table. I'm just a great dog with specific requirements!  No dogs, iffy on kids, no cats.  Just you and a big fenced yard to play ball.  You wouldn't even have to walk me if you throw the ball.  I also love walking with you in the yard and you can kick the ball!  I have fantastic recall:  all you have to do is whistle and I stop to look at you or yell "Haze".  And if you are lonely too, we'd be the bestest buddies!

Say "Ball"and I bring it right to you. Say "Drop" and the ball is at your feet. And I love to play Tug with my favorite rope.  Just over 7 years old and wonderfully obedient, I'm energetic, playful, and  loving.  Say "Sit" and my behind hits the ground.  Say "Down" and my belly's on the ground. Need an alarm dog? I have a BIG bark. I'm good on a leash and very good off-leash. Just say "Haze!" and I come right to you.   Come see me & we just might hit it off! I just know that there is a lonesome person who needs me too!

I'm house trained and crate trained, and should have an experienced big dog owner.  But I love men or women. I am  fine with older teenagers but not children.

Up to date on age appropriate vaccines, neutered and micro-chipped.


***Haze is available for meet and greets with potential adopters by appointment only.*** (T&WL/CM*)

Adoption Fee: $100.00

attributes.descriptionHtml: Meet King! King came to us when his owner decided he could no longer care for him. He has spent his whole life living in a pen outdoors so everything is new to him. He's still a little on the shy side but is making huge strides in learning to adjust to his new found love and attention. King and Queen are wonderful dogs around 11-12 years. They will take some time to adjust to a new home.  They came from an extreme neglect situation and are doing well with me but still skittish around new situations or people.  It is amazing how resilient animals are!  They were malnourished and living in a pen for years with little human contact.  They love other dogs and will play for hours but will wait to come in the door until the coast is clear of humans.  They do not love the human touch but will tolerate it and show no aggression when touched, just discomfort.   King and Queen will thrive in a calm, quiet household with another dog and lots of love.  King and Queen are very bonded and i fear might regress if separated.Come meet King and give him the home that he deserves.For more information: releashedrescue@gmail.com

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, my name is Franklin and I am about 8 years old.  I am a special needs cat.  I have been adopted and returned 2 times because I suffer from urinary issues.  I have been diagnosed with feline idiopathic cystitis (FIC).   Signs of this syndrome are bloody urine, straining to urinate and urinating in unusual places.  I am on a strict diet of cat food manufactured specifically to eliminate crystals in the urine.  I have been x-rayed for bladder stones.  The x-rays showed no bladder stones.  The most important thing for me is to drink plenty of water.  Since I was returned I have not had any urination problems.  I am an affectionate cat and like to cuddle.  I am playful. My favorite game is chasing a laser light.   I also like to chase and catch mice. My adopter said the cutest thing about me is the way I look at her and I have the best personality ever.   I am available for immediate adoption to a family that understands my condition and work with me.  My adoption fee is by donation.  I am neutered, UTD on vaccinations, tested for FeLV/FIV, treated for internal and external parasites and microchipped.  If you are interested in adopting me please complete an adoption profile in person or on-line at www.bondcohs.petfinder.com.  Email the completed profile to the address provided.  A copy of our policy regarding warranties, refunds or returns is available upon request.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
When Nancy was diagnosed with glaucoma, she required surgery to remove both eyes. :( Considering she has no sight, she does remarkably well in her special foster home, but EHR would love for her to be in an adults-only foster (or forever) home where her condition could be best managed. She can be a little picky about her doggie friends, but is okay with some dogs. EHR's wish is that someone would take Nancy into their home as foster or forever pup & let her live out the rest of her days knowing love and security with people she trusts.

Nancy is a scruffy little girl with great big ears and a thirst for adventure! She is super easy on leash and loves going for walks and exploring the great outdoors. She also loves playing with her toys. Nancy takes treats gently and knows some basic commands. But like many terriers, she has a strong personality and would do best with an experienced owner. 

Here's what one of her kennel buddies said about Nancy:  She got in and rode extremely well in the car.  On the walk itself, she was initially so excited to be out that she pulled in different directions, but because she is so light it was very easy to manage.  She settled down quickly, however, and was great on the leash for the rest of the walk.  She loves to stop and smell everything like a typical terrier but kept the pace and walked well.

A special girl like Nancy requires a special kind of adopter. If you feel that you could be that special person who could foster or adopt Nancy, please fill out an application at www.ehrdogs.org and be sure to mention her name….NANCY STEELE!!
attributes.descriptionText:
When Nancy was diagnosed with glaucoma, she required surgery to remove both eyes. :( Considering she has no sight, she does remarkably well in her special foster home, but EHR would love for her to be in an adults-only foster (or forever) home where her condition could be best managed. She can be a little picky about her doggie friends, but is okay with some dogs. EHR's wish is that someone would take Nancy into their home as foster or forever pup & let her live out the rest of her days knowing love and security with people she trusts.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Calypso is a lovely, happy girl with a wonderful tortoiseshell coat of many colors - you can't get any cuter than this little darling!  She is very playful, curious and affectionate.

Sweet Calypso is a delight to have around, and she is hoping for a loving family to adopt and spoil her.  She is quite a player, so it would be nice if she was adopted into a home that has another cat  who loves to play as well.  We guarantee if you meet her you will fall in love. She is pleasant, and likes to talk to you.  She calls from across the room when she sees you.

To meet Calypso, go to our website, www.happycatadoptions.org and under her photo, click the adoption link to fill out the online application.

Calypso came from a local shelter where she and her mom were on death row. Her mom has been  adopted, and now Calypso needs a furrever home as well.

For more information, contact her foster directly at haroldw1@sbcglobal.net or leave a voicemail at for a return call.

Her adoption fee of $125 will help to rescue other kitties.

History:
Mr. Orange came to us originally in July of 2013 as an stray drop off when a good samaritan found him. He was adopted twice so far in his time here and both times ended up at the humane society, through no fault of his own, who then transferred him back to us. 

Personality:
Mr. Orange is quite the character and is a staff and volunteer favorite around here. This dashingly handsome orange boy is not hard to fall in love with once you get past his gruff exterior. Mr. Orange likes to make people think he's a big tough boy but he really love chin scratches and even likes being brushed if you know the right spots. He will need a cat experienced owner who knows how to pay attention to his ques on when he wants his alone time. Hopefully Mr. Orange can find another chance at happily ever after soon cause he truly deserves a forever after his rough past.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Kale originally came to EHR as a puppy back in 2013 with his sibling Kandy. He was quickly adopted and renamed Max. 6 years later, this boy was returned to EHR through no fault of his own.

 

Max is a big man that loves to run around his yard, play fetch with his unstuffed toys, and sunbathe.  After a long day running around, he loves to cuddle up on the couch with his family.

 

 

He's best suited for a family with older children and a fenced-in yard. He does not do well with other animals, and must be kept separate from other dogs. When he meets new people, he gets so excited, will jump on them and give lots of kisses. Max is housebroken, not destructive, and is calm and relaxed in the home.  He is cuddly and loves belly rubs. He knows some simple commands, including sit and paw. Max is good on a leash, but does get excited if he sees other animals. He needs to be walked on a harness.

 

 

If you would like to meet this boy, please fill out a Dog Adoption Application at www.ehrdogs.org & be sure to ask for MAX (KALE) SCAS! He sure would love to be in a home again!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Lucy is a beautiful little Boxer girl who loves going for walks and playing outdoors.  She’s had a fair amount of training and knows her basic commands, but as with any dog, she could use an owner who will keep up her training.

Lucy is cautious upon meeting new people but once she trusts you, her loving side shines through.  She has a strong personality that requires an experienced dog owner. Lucy loves to go for rides in the car, walks at the park, swimming, playing with her toys, and spending time with her favorite volunteers. She has spent far too long waiting for her forever family to come along (almost 7 years in the shelter...). Adopters  are often turned off by the fact that she will require multiple meets to learn its ok to trust you. Will anybody take the time to love Lucy..?

If you’d be interested in meeting Lucy, please fill out an application and be sure to mention her name!
